title: Palacio - Wikipedia
text: Palacio Appearance Look up palacio in Wiktionary, the free dictionary. Palacio (palace) is a Spanish habitational name. It may have originated from many places in Spain, especially in Galicia and Asturias.[1] Notable people with the surname include: - Agustina Palacio de Libarona (1825–1880), Argentine writer, storyteller, heroine - Alberto Palacio, engineer - Alfredo Palacio (1939–2025), Ecuadorian cardiologist and politician, president of Ecuador (2005–2007) - Andy Palacio, Belizean musician - Emilio Palacio, Ecuadorian journalist - Ernesto Palacio, opera singer - Héctor Palacio, Colombian road racing cyclist - Milt Palacio, basketball player - R. J. Palacio, American writer of the 2012 children's novel Wonder - Rodrigo Palacio, footballer See also [edit]References [edit]- ^ Hanks, Patrick (8 May 2003). Dictionary of American Family Names. Oxford University Press. p. 40. ISBN 978-0-19-977169-1.
